To make a button triggerable by a keyboard key, you can add a key event listener to the document or a specific element that listens for a particular key press and then triggers the button's click event when that key is pressed. Here's a basic example using JavaScript:

Assuming you have a button with an ID of `myButton`, you can add the following JavaScript code:

```javascript
document.addEventListener('keydown', function(event) {
    if (event.key === "Enter") {  // You can change "Enter" to any key you prefer
        var button = document.getElementById('myButton');
        button.click();
    }
});
```

This script listens for a keydown event across the entire document. When the "Enter" key (or any key you specify) is pressed, it simulates a click on the button with the ID `myButton`.

